title: Grateful Dead Live at Universal Amphitheatre on 1973-07-01
description:
Set 1

Mississippi Half Step, Me & My Uncle, Sugaree, The Race is On, Brown Eyed Women, Looks Like Rain, Don't Ease Me In, Big River, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Around & Around

Set 2

Playin' In The Band, Row Jimmy, El Paso, Loose Lucy, Truckin'-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Me And Bobby McGee, Casey Jones

reviews.review_text:
Killer upgrade Thank you Charlie Miller!

5* b/c I don't know what could be a whole lot better than a clean '73 Miller board.  Those Big Rivers are unstoppable.  I don't know how Jer could have not liked it and jammed on it like that.  Might have been some sarcasm there?

Combine with Kaslow/MOTB for sweet matrix!  I would if I could, but I just cain't shoot that good.

Awesome '73 show The soundboard mix is excellent. Great transfer by Mr. Miller as usual.

China->Rider is sublime. Early Loose Lucy at a slower pace has a great feel.
What a 3 Day Run Highlights: Playing In The Band, The Other One

row donna i always  cringe to hear folks  sayin how donna was always  out of tune...
as if  the rest of the boys had sung perfect pitch,  please...

you know ,  you have to understand just how hard it is to hear  oneself, his or herself,  when you're singing live,  with lot s of  amplified  amplifications,  i mean the amps, not  the drugs

eventually they gave up trying to hear themselves through monitors, went to in ears

anyway,  this is  a great  performance of donna doin it  ,  and  you   have to understand that  basically ,  anyone who can hear themselfes  is gonna  sing  decently,  but not if you can't

when a singer is out of tune,  that  is usually the reason,  it's  not hearing oneself, the  curse of singing with electric  and drums, etc.,  

luckily they had  good monitors  and  at least sometimes  sound  just  fucking great, like here

Not Too Fast, and Not Too Slow Speechless.

Peace ~ Nick.
